1. About

  Portable Abstracted Network Library (libpanet).
  Developed by Pedro A. Hortas (pah@ucodev.org).
  Home page: http://www.ucodev.org


2. Briefing

  libpanet is an abstraction layer for portable network level programming.
  It's tiny, simple and portable for most of the mainstream operating systems, including Microsoft Windows.


3. Version

  $ cat VERSION


4. Documentation

  $ cat doc/overview.txt


5. Build and Install

  # ./do
  # ./install

  Alternatively, to enable support for libfsma, do:

  # ./do fsma
  # ./install


